# vsc-orca

VS Code extension for the Orca ecosystem. Provides IDE integration for fetching execution bundles, submitting evidence, and running tasks.

## Tech Stack

- TypeScript, VS Code extension API (`@types/vscode`, engine `^1.85.0`)
- Build: esbuild
- Node 20+

## Structure

- `src/extension.ts` — Activation, command/view registration
- `src/api-client.ts` — Orca API client (fetch-based)
- `src/status-bar.ts` — Status bar controller
- `src/prompt.ts` — Prompt handling
- `src/types.ts` — Shared types
- `src/views/bundle-tree.ts` — Sidebar TreeDataProvider for bundles
- `src/commands/` — Command implementations:
  - `fetch-bundle.ts`, `pick-bundle.ts`, `submit-evidence.ts`, `execute-task.ts`

## VS Code Patterns

- Register commands via `vscode.commands.registerCommand`
- Tree views implement `vscode.TreeDataProvider`
- Extension config in `package.json` under `contributes` (commands, views, configuration)
- Use `context.subscriptions.push()` for disposable cleanup

## Parent Project

Part of the Orca ecosystem. The main API lives in the `orca` monorepo.
